{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-js","path":"/eng/backend/19-09-01/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>When developing web applications that various users access, there are time-related tasks such as post creation time, login time, and comment timestamps that need to be handled. While you can use built-in DB server functions like NOW(), these outputs are not particularly intuitive for users to read, and if the server's timezone differs from your local timezone, the displayed time may not match what you expect. To address this, let's explore the moment.js module, which provides both user-friendly formatting and the ability to output time in your desired timezone.</p>\n<h3 id=\"standard-time\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#standard-time\" aria-label=\"standard time permalink\" class=\"anchor-header before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Standard Time</h3>\n<p>Before using the module, we need to understand some basic background about standard time. If you use the time-related methods built into your DB server or JavaScript without a module, you'll see abbreviations like GMT, UTC, UTC+9, and so on. These abbreviations are related to standard time systems.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>GMT: Stands for Greenwich Mean Time, which is the mean solar time based on the Royal Observatory in Greenwich, England.</li>\n<li>UTC: Stands for Universal Time, Coordinated, which is a time standard based on cesium atomic vibration frequency.</li>\n<li>UTC+9: UTC base time plus 9 hours, which is equivalent to Korean Standard Time.</li>\n<li>KST: Stands for Korean Standard Time, the standard time of South Korea.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Some countries also use DST (Daylight Saving Time) for certain periods. It stands for Daylight Saving Time and means advancing the standard time by one hour during the summer months.</p>\n<h3 id=\"momentjs-basics\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#momentjs-basics\" aria-label=\"momentjs basics permalink\" class=\"anchor-header before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>moment.js Basics</h3>\n<p>Install the module using npm and declare moment.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"javascript\"><pre class=\"language-javascript\"><code class=\"language-javascript\">npm install <span class=\"token operator\">--</span>save moment\n<span class=\"token keyword\">var</span> moment <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token function\">require</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'moment'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<ol>\n<li>Let's print the current time to the console. (When I ran it, I got: Sun Sep 01 2019 10:41:04 GMT+0900.)</li>\n</ol>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"javascript\"><pre class=\"language-javascript\"><code class=\"language-javascript\">console<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token template-string\"><span class=\"token template-punctuation string\">`</span><span class=\"token interpolation\"><span class=\"token interpolation-punctuation punctuation\">${</span><span class=\"token function\">moment</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token interpolation-punctuation punctuation\">}</span></span><span class=\"token template-punctuation string\">`</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<ol start=\"2\">\n<li>You can achieve more intuitive output with the following code. YYYY, MM, DD hold the year, month, and day, while HH, mm, ss hold the hours, minutes, and seconds.</li>\n</ol>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"javascript\"><pre class=\"language-javascript\"><code class=\"language-javascript\">console<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token template-string\"><span class=\"token template-punctuation string\">`</span><span class=\"token interpolation\"><span class=\"token interpolation-punctuation punctuation\">${</span> <span class=\"token function\">moment</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">format</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"YYYY-MM-DD HH:mm:ss\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token interpolation-punctuation punctuation\">}</span></span><span class=\"token template-punctuation string\">`</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<ol start=\"3\">\n<li>If you want to print individual values such as month, day, day of the week, or time separately, use the following code:</li>\n</ol>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"javascript\"><pre class=\"language-javascript\"><code class=\"language-javascript\">console<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token template-string\"><span class=\"token template-punctuation string\">`</span><span class=\"token interpolation\"><span class=\"token interpolation-punctuation punctuation\">${</span> <span class=\"token function\">moment</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">month</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token interpolation-punctuation punctuation\">}</span></span><span class=\"token template-punctuation string\">`</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\nconsole<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token template-string\"><span class=\"token template-punctuation string\">`</span><span class=\"token interpolation\"><span class=\"token interpolation-punctuation punctuation\">${</span> <span class=\"token function\">moment</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">date</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token interpolation-punctuation punctuation\">}</span></span><span class=\"token template-punctuation string\">`</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\nconsole<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token template-string\"><span class=\"token template-punctuation string\">`</span><span class=\"token interpolation\"><span class=\"token interpolation-punctuation punctuation\">${</span> <span class=\"token function\">moment</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">day</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token interpolation-punctuation punctuation\">}</span></span><span class=\"token template-punctuation string\">`</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<ol start=\"4\">\n<li>Features like \"posted X days ago\" can be implemented with the code below. It tells you how many days have passed since a reference time.</li>\n</ol>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"javascript\"><pre class=\"language-javascript\"><code class=\"language-javascript\">console<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token template-string\"><span class=\"token template-punctuation string\">`</span><span class=\"token interpolation\"><span class=\"token interpolation-punctuation punctuation\">${</span> <span class=\"token function\">moment</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">diff</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token function\">moment</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'2019-08-01'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span><span class=\"token string\">\"days\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token interpolation-punctuation punctuation\">}</span></span><span class=\"token template-punctuation string\">`</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<h3 id=\"moment-timezone\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#moment-timezone\" aria-label=\"moment timezone permalink\" class=\"anchor-header before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>moment-timezone</h3>\n<p>If you're working on a server that isn't located in your local timezone rather than your own computer, the time may be displayed differently. This is where the moment-timezone module comes in. After installing both the moment and moment-timezone modules, simply set the timezone of your declared moment to the desired region.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"javascript\"><pre class=\"language-javascript\"><code class=\"language-javascript\">npm install <span class=\"token operator\">--</span>save moment\nnpm install <span class=\"token operator\">--</span>save moment<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>timezone\n<span class=\"token keyword\">var</span> moment <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token function\">require</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'moment'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token function\">require</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'moment-timezone'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\nmoment<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>tz<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">setDefault</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"Asia/Seoul\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<h3 id=\"reference\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#reference\" aria-label=\"reference permalink\" class=\"anchor-header before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Reference</h3>\n<p>Beyond displaying time in a user-friendly format in Node.js, if you're curious about the overall concept of timezones or JavaScript's Date object, the resources below may be helpful.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://meetup.toast.com/posts/125\">Toast meetup! - Handling Timezones in JavaScript (1)</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://meetup.toast.com/posts/130\">Toast meetup! - Handling Timezones in JavaScript (2)</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://momentjs.com/timezone/\">moment-timezone Official Website</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://devstory.ibksplatform.com/2018/01/nodejs-momentjs.html\">Nodejs Date-Related moment.js</a></li>\n</ul>","tableOfContents":"<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#standard-time\">Standard Time</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#momentjs-basics\">moment.js Basics</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#moment-timezone\">moment-timezone</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#reference\">Reference</a></li>\n</ul>","frontmatter":{"path":"/backend/19-09-01/","title":"Working with Time Using the moment.js Library","category":"BackEnd","date":"2019-09-01"}}},"pageContext":{"postPath":"/backend/19-09-01/","language":"eng","langRegex":"/contents/eng/"}},"staticQueryHashes":["2145088972","256249292","63159454"],"slicesMap":{}}